Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Pour 300ml cold salted @water{300%ml} (double for 4p) into a medium #pot with a tight-fitting #lid.

Stir in the @Jasmine Rice{150%grams} and bring to the boil.

Once boiling, lower the heat to medium, cover with the lid and cook for ~{12%minutes}.

Remove the pot from the heat and keep covered for another ~{12%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @Garlic{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press).

In a large #bowl, combine the garlic, @Breadcrumbs{1%pack}, ¼ tsp @salt{¼%tsp} and @water{2%tbsp} (double for 4p).

Add the @Irish Beef Mince{240%grams}, season with @pepper{to taste} and mix together by hand.

Roll into evenly-sized balls, 3-4 per person. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Pop the beef meatballs onto a large (lined) #baking tray{}.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until browned on the outside and cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Meatballs are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, place a pan over medium heat (without oil).

Once hot, dry-fry the @Sesame Seeds{1%sachet} until lightly toasted, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove from the #pan and set aside.

Trim the @Carrot{1}(trimmed), halve lengthways (no need to peel) and slice widthways into 1cm chunks.

Return the pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of @Oil{to taste}.

Fry the carrot for ~{4-5%minutes}. Add the @Broccolini{75%grams} and fry for ~{2-3%minutes} more. Add a splash of @Water{to taste}, cover and cook until tender, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Once the veg is tender, remove the lid, stir in the @Teriyaki Sauce{2%sachets} along with 50ml water (double for 4p). Ensure everything is well coated.

Add the cooked meatballs to the pan.

Stir together and cook until the sauce has thickened slightly and everything is piping hot, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Taste and season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} if needed. Add a splash more water if the sauce becomes too thick.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork and share between #bowls{}.

Top with your teriyaki beef meatballs and veg.

Finish with a sprinkling of sesame seeds.